            <p>McDonald's: A classic choice for fast food. </p>
            <p>Starbucks: Your go-to for coffee and light snacks. </p>
            <p>These are great options for a quick meal before you head to security or after you land. </p>
            <h2>After Security (Post-Security) – Where the Real Feast Begins! </h2>
            <p>Once you clear the security, the options expand significantly across Concourse A and Concourse B. </p>
            <h3><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right-long"></i> In Concourse A (Gates A2-A21): </h3>
            <p>From this concourse, you can find mixed places, coffee shops, bars, and casual dining options. Various eateries are offering quick salads, sandwiches, and hotel meals. If you are feeling lazy, then enjoy a bold hotel coffee at Starbucks. </p>
            <h3><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right-long"></i> In Concourse B (Gates B20-B55): </h3>
            <p>This concourse is the central hub of <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/delta-airlines-reservations.aspx"><b>Delta Airlines</b></a>, and you will find the widest and often most exciting food choices here. There are also sit-down restaurants here, including The Palm Bar and Grille, that offer a classic American steakhouse experience, great for a more substantial meal. Le Grand Comptoir has the option of stylish wine and a European feel, which provides a small plate and a sophisticated atmosphere. </p>
            <h2>Tips for Finding Your Perfect Meal: </h2>
            <p>You can check the digital boards because once you look for the digital airport maps and screen throughout the terminal, you can find the list of all the restaurants and shops, along with their locations and often their operating hours. You can also use the airport website or app, and JFK's official webpage usually has a detailed directory of all food outlets in T4. Some airlines or airport apps might also allow you to browse menus or even pre-order. </p>
